flowchart LR
    A([Start: User in Azure Portal]) --> B[Search and select Terraform service]
    B --> C[Click Get Started]

    C --> D[Azure sets expectations\nHCP Terraform executes\nAzure handles discovery, governance, management]
    D --> E[Connect to HCP Terraform organization\nOAuth or SSO]

    E --> F[Azure verifies org permissions and workspace presence]
    F --> G{Choose onboarding mode}

    G -->|Option A| H[Connect existing workspaces\nPrimary path]
    G -->|Option B| X[Import unmanaged Azure resources\nFuture or limited scope]

    H --> I[Azure discovers eligible workspaces\nAzureRM provider, target subscriptions, run health]
    I --> J[User selects workspaces to connect]

    J --> K[Map each workspace to Azure scope\nSubscription or management group\nEnvironment and owner]
    K --> L[Azure validates credentials and allowed scope]

    L --> M[Configure trust\nManaged identity plus OIDC federation]
    M --> N[Non-destructive validation\nState health and resource ownership]

    N --> O{Enable optional Azure governance controls?}
    O -->|Yes| P[Apply policy checks, approvals, limits, and cost signals]
    O -->|No| Q[Skip governance controls]

    P --> R[Register Terraform stacks as Azure RP resources\nMicrosoft.Terraform/stacks and environments]
    Q --> R

    R --> S[Confirmation\nShow status, ownership metadata, and links to HCP deep actions]
    S --> T([Outcome: Connected infrastructure in Azure\nNo Terraform apply unless explicitly requested])

    X --> Y([Deferred path for future rollout])